 For "history" is, in another guise, one of the classic forms that the
 museum's governing "fiction" takes, and its imbrication with memory
 is strategic and contingent rather than unidirectional. As Donato has
 so persuasively argued, the museum fiction results from "uncritical
 belief" in the representational power of ordering and classification,
