 series of objects to series of labels." 7 Conceived as an activity, history,
 of course, involves such ordering and classification, but so, in differ-
 ent ways, does memory, of which metonymy must be taken as one of
 the essential tropes.8
 Any critique, but especially one involving institutions so explic-
 itly concerned with these categories, must take both the dialogics and
 the interrelations of history and memory, museal and memorial, ob-
