 configurations these relationships are what such museums produce,
 what is ultimately at stake in their construction as institutions. In this
 case, institutions such as war museums base their self-definition in
 large part on a distinction, conceptually akin to Nora's, between the
 museal and the memorial. The perceived spontaneity and instability
