 de la France et de l'horreur de lAllemagne et de lAllemand." Though
 he made several other references to "la Haine sacree contre nos enne-
 mis" he went on to characterize the couple's collecting policy as one
 of absolute impartiality: Madame Leblanc even paid visits to neutral
 countries in order to purchase documentary materials from France's
 enemies.'9
